snippet: The Shabab, claimed responsibility for an attack that killed at least 11 people and wounded 15 others in an explosion on Wednesday in Mogadishu, officials and witnesses said.
abstract: Suicide car bomber kills at least 11 people and wounds 15 others in an explosion in Mogadishu, Somalia; Shabab, an Islamist group that has pledged allegiance to Al Qaeda, claims responsibility.
lead_paragraph: The Shabab, claimed responsibility for an attack that killed at least 11 people and wounded 15 others in an explosion on Wednesday in Mogadishu, officials and witnesses said.
